value.0: Eav Mottonel is one of Lord Valerius' apprentices, and she has the dubious honor of manning the very face of his operations at the Twilight Praxeum. Bearing a rather bored expression and studying any who enter the Umbral Cantina with a stern gaze, she has little hesitation in drawing her lightsabers to cut down any who dare disturb the peace with a swift lack of mercy. As a Sith Warrior, she is known to have been an ardent student of Juyo.

The Revanites are a splinter faction of Malak’s Sith Empire. After Revan’s fall, they are those who took issue with Malak’s new, more destructive war, and threw in with Lord Valerius, supporting his rebellion against the Darth and bid to claim the title of Dark Lord of the Sith. For some their loyalty is to Valerius, others to their idea of who Revan was and what he stood for, others simply take issue with Darth Malak, and some still seek out the Revanites for their less despicable tendencies as far as Sith go, seeing them more as the Jedi Crusaders of the late Mandalorian Wars than the monsters that compose the Sith Empire. Regardless, they are still followers of the Dark Side.

A Revanite guard serves as one of the elite soldiers in support of Lord Valerius, and they are oft seen either guarding the Twilight Praxeum or afield on operations.

Regardless, they are still followers of the Dark Side.

The Revanites promote competition amongst their ranks, both among the Force Sensitives among their number and their rank and file troops. Those the most merciless, cruel and powerful amongst them are elevated, while those exhibiting softer tendencies are treated like fodder and find death sooner rather than later - often from friendly fire.

These are the former among them. Clad in finer armor and given access to the newest in Imperial weapons technology as reward for their faithful service to the Sith.

Aarec Gaeir is a flamboyant and gregarious man, one with warm smiles and a twinkle in his eyes as if he harbored a galactic secret that he is but dying to share. Once a smuggler and blockade runner, he caught Lord Valerius' eyes with his efficient deliveries, and was shortly after offered an official position as the proprietor and bartender of the Twilight Praxeum's Umbral Cantina. For reasons perhaps known only to himself, he accepted the offer, and is known both for organizing tournaments in the cantina's arena as well as being one of the few non-Force Sensitives that has Lord Valerius' personal holo-communicator codes.

The Twilight Praxeum holds many hangars and dockyards, and these blastdoors lead to the rest of the hangar bay...

One of the many hangars of the Twilight Praxeum. This one is intended more for civilian use, and mercantile operations, with the Revanite Order drawing in trickles of blockade runners and smugglers to deliver supplies necessary for the continued renovations of Lord Valerius' pet project. 

Beyond, one could see signs of other ships of the Revanite fleet, patrolling the perimeter of the Twilight Praxeum.
Board a shuttle to head from the Twilight Praxeum to the Revanite lake base on Viscara...
An ale brewed by the Gamorrean's using a secret recipe. Hard hitting and taste's like shit but guaranteed to get you drunk fast.
Created by a coruscant local, this ale tastes sweet and is easy to drink.
A bitter white wine that is popular along side a bantha steak.
A shot of liquor that is infused with a small portion of bacta. Guaranteed to get one drunk and feeling healthier at the same time.
A simple cigar. Light it up and have a puff.
A cigarette. Bad for the body bud good for the nerves.
A beautiful red wine brewed on Corellia. It's sweet taste comes from the raspberry's that are infused inside.
A small pink shot served in a diamond glass... because it eats through anything else in seconds.  Only for the strongest constitutions, and most crazed minds.
Not even the bartenders know what goes into these drinks. All they know is it comes in a giant metal barrel and tastes delicious.
A drink that resembles a reactor core if you look down into the drink. It's quite better but goes down easy.
Bantha milk, vodka and dark chocolate make up sith spit. Tastes good and easy to make, a staple in most bars.
A cider made primaly from citrus fruit gathered somewhere on viscara.
Orange with a bit of lime for those that don't want to drink alcohol but still wanna look cool. *Thumbs up*
A drink that's contents are still unknown, but when drunken, makes the consumer want to get naked and dance.
A teal-colored, bubbly wine that is produced on the planet of Alderaan and served across the galaxy.
An ale created by trandoshan prisoners in a toilet on Coruscant. Now brewed professionally and sold across the galaxy but no one but trandoshans can stomach it.
A glass of high quality H20. This used to be named "Simply Pilgrim" but the bars went back to the original name of water.
White Wampa is simply vodka, milk and snow. Often served on Hoth at large gatherings, but can be served in bars using shaved ice instead of snow.
This drink doesn't behave like a usual liquid.  It's constantly swirling into new shapes, as if going to climb out of the mug, before collapsing into liquid again.  Unnerving.
A double shot of malt whisky with several ice cubes. This drink is a delicacy all throughout the galaxy and only the sophisticated drink such a perfect drink.
